<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6007&amp;p=26514#p26514"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Metro Color Tool  (Win 7 style)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6007&amp;p=26514#p26514"><![CDATA[
I made this Metro Color tool skin to help people understand Win 10,<br />which has special color tables, that it works from, to color the menu.<br />I don't know which ones are best. I included a bunch to pick as options.<br />There are lots more.<br />It would be too much to put every color as an option to try out.<br />If this wets your appetite, you can download the Classic Shell utility to see all the colors available.<br />You can make a personalized skin for yourself, and upload to show the world. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> <br /><br /><br />As this is a limited testing tool, you may find selector buttons too light, dark, or even disappear.<br />It's because I did not make color options for selector buttons. Separators stay same too. Fixed some of them.<br />I made it for better understanding of Ivos Metro skin, which this is modded from. <br /><br />You can use it as a stand alone skin, if you want.<br />Upon info from Ivo, there can be 4 different colors on a bitmap mask. Black, Red, Green, and blue colors can be used as masks,<br />to reference any color available. <br />Can be a regular hex color example &quot; #00FFFF &quot; or a Metro color &quot; $StartSelectionBackground &quot;. <br />To make the Metro color work, the additional dollar sign &quot; $ &quot; is put in front of Metro color text. <br /><br />I made skin to have a gradient bar at top, and left and right columns with different colors.<br />You can pick different colors for left top bar, and right top bar to give it a gradient. Or just make every color same.<br />Up to you to experiment.<br /><br /><br /><span style="color:#0000ff;">EDIT:  When Windows introduced Dark theme in update, it changed what was black to white.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="color:#0000ff;">To see black as black, turn off Dark app mode in Windows color settings.</span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue May 10, 2016 2:33 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
